@francis0407  `select count(*) from t group by 1` is indeed different from `select count(*) from t`. But it can't be the reason to keep **THIS** `1` here.

The former `1` represents the first column which is handling well somewhere, while the latter represents a constant could be eliminated. 

`select count(*) from t group by '2020-03-21'` is same as `select count(*) from t` semantically.
